			<ns0:name>halya...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/112856509894568708731/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">test_interrupt test sends to debug stub 2 commands at first: continue command that is followed by interrupt. Since continue command is send at the start of program execution, interrupt can catch program in syscall called by IRT (currently it is nacl_tls_init which calls second_tls_set syscall). Then test_interrupt tries to single step program in this state what is equivalent to continue command. Since test loops forever this leads to hang.

This was uncovered by debug stub speed up.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-12-30T13:50:57.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2012-12-29T13:44:11.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Fixed</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
